So I thought about making some small change to easily get start on such tasks:
Firstly: The function that does most (or all) of processing is `process_word`,
so we'll stick that in first and then make sure the rest uses it. For example
`get_letter_freqs`, which will return a dictionary mapping letters to counts.
Secondly, one way to process each word is by splitting them on whitespace:
we get a list (or tuple) of words. So, I changed `process_word` so that instead
of returning the processed string itself we return an iterable over tokens,
which is something much more useful for downstream processing (including further
processing!).
This way it's easy to process each word in turn.
Thirdly: For a simple task like this one, it makes sense to also write a helper function which does nothing
